OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1781097082
OL,3,CPrimary students crowned Britain's
OL,4,Cfunniest class by Beano
OL,6,FIn the end, it was joy Lane's Boyce
OL,7,FClass who took glory with the line: "I
OL,8,Fdidn't think food could make calls,
OL,9,Fbut then: boom! Onion rings".
OL,11,FThe joke received 34% of the national
OL,12,Fvote, pipping runners up from schools
OL,13,Fin Leyton and Edinburgh with "What is
OL,14,Fa school uniform's favourite food? Tie
OL,15,Ffood!" and "What do you call a bedtime
OL,16,Fcheese? Pyjama-san!".
OL,18,FBoyce Class teacher Bethan Crowe was
OL,19,Falso crowned Britain's Funniest
OL,20,FTeacher alongside her students.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
